From Brad Templeton Subject Re Secret algorithm Re Clipper Chip and crypto key escrow One presumes the system could work as follows a Blank clips are manufactured by Mykotronx and The number produced is carefully audited and they are shipped to the first escrow It programs the chips with its half the key and prints out a paper slip with the key half and non secret chip serial The reams of paper are filed in locked boxes in the vault a fuse is burnt in the chip so that the key is now The chip then goes to the next escrow house where the same thing is This continues through N escrow houses perhaps could be more than The last one provides the chip to the cellular phone And yes this has to be a public key system or it would be almost impossible to It might not be RSA but that does not mean that PKP doesn't get Until PKP has the patent on the general concept of public key encryption as well as the particular implementation known as Brad Templeton ClariNet Communications Sunnyvale CA